  "prompt": "What is the recruitment process of Accenture?",
  "response": "Accenture's recruitment process typically involves several stages:\n\n1. Online Application\n- Submit resume/CV through Accenture's career website\n- Fill out detailed application form\n- Provide personal and professional details\n\n2. Initial Screening\n- Resume screening by HR\n- Matching candidate's profile with job requirements\n- Checking educational and professional qualifications\n\n3. Online Assessment/Aptitude Test\n- Psychometric tests\n- Analytical and logical reasoning\n- Numerical and verbal ability tests\n- Technical skills assessment (for technical roles)\n\n4. Technical/HR Interview Rounds\n- First round: HR/screening interview\n- Technical interview (for technical positions)\n- In-depth discussion of skills and experience\n- Behavioral and situational questions\n- Assessment of cultural fit\n\n5. Video/Virtual Interview\n- Interview conducted via video conferencing\n- Panel or one-on-one interview format\n\n6. Final Interview\n- Senior management/leadership round\n- Final evaluation of candidate's potential\n- Negotiation of compensation and role\n\n7. Background Verification\n- Reference checks\n- Educational qualification verification\n- Previous employment verification\n\n8. Job Offer\n- Extending formal offer letter\n- Discussing joining date and other details\n\nThe specific stages might vary slightly depending on the role and location.",
